# Styling Guidelines

## TailwindCSS Requirements

- Always use Tailwind classes for styling HTML elements
- Avoid using direct CSS or style tags whenever possible
- Use Tailwind instead of direct CSS styling as much as possible
- Use `class:` instead of the ternary operator in class tags whenever possible

## CSS File Management

- Do NOT use any .css file from static folder directly in the project
- Instead, use static CSS files as a reference to re-write the CSS using Tailwind classes
- Reference files in [static/css/](mdc:static/css/) for styling inspiration but implement with Tailwind

## Static Directory Reference

The project contains reference CSS files in the static directory:
- [main.css](mdc:static/css/main.css)
- [style.css](mdc:static/css/style.css) 
- [styles.css](mdc:static/css/styles.css)
- [docs.css](mdc:static/css/docs.css)
- [flexboxgrid.min.css](mdc:static/css/flexboxgrid.min.css)

Use these as visual reference but implement styling with Tailwind classes.